Naming convention:

[Letter A - K] [Number 1 - 13] - direction (n, w, e, s - can be NE or SW, etc) ('PTZ' might be there, or its '[Letter A - K] PTZ') - Berth/Block/TELs/Wall St/Reefer rack/Rail/Pedestal/Flipline/Plug Reefer/Airlocks/CEG/AssetMangement/Exit Fuel [Number]
Causeway Sign #X
ADM Parking
TEL 01 - 144
FleetView Recording
[Letter A - K ] - [Letter A - K]

examples:
A10 - NE - Berth 404
A2 - B
A8 - SE PTZ - Block 1F
G13 - C PTZ - Block 4A
J10 - A PTZ North - Plug Reefer
TEL 118
K11 - D PTZ - Exit Fuel


What something being present in the name means and how it should be used when determining the rules for checking that camera:
[] Berth  - humans allowed (with vest and helmet), check for container hazards (misalignment, open doors) and vehicles at unsafe distance
[] Block  - No humans, check container and vehicle hazards
[] TELs - humans allowed (just vest), check for container hazards and possibly humans stepping outside of designated trucker spot
[] Wall St - No humans, check container hazards and vehicle proximity
[] Reefer rack - No humans, check container hazards
[] Rail  - No humans, check container hazards
[] Pedestal  - No humans, check container hazards
[] Flipline  - No humans, check container hazards
[] Plug Reefer  - No humans, check container and vehicle hazards
[] Airlocks  - (unsure)
[] CEG  - (unsure)
[] AssetManagement  - Humans in vests possibly, check vehicle hazards (unsure)
[] Exit Fuel  - Vests, check vehicle hazards
TEL  - Vests mandatory, humans only in dedicated spot and going to-from truck

